In a soup pot, cook sausage over medium heat until no pink remains. Add onions, celery, and carrots. Cook uncovered for 5 minutes, or until onions are soft. Add tomatoes, chicken broth, cabbage, and basil. Bring to a boil. Stir in macaroni, and cover. Simmer for 10 minutes, or until pasta is tender. Season with garlic salt. Serve.